---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms & Conditions | SciCalcX Online Computational Suite" description="Review the SciCalcX Terms and Conditions. Learn about usage guidelines, licensing, and disclaimers.">
  <div class="w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-6 sm:space-y-8 font-sans">
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <div class="text-center md:text-left space-y-1.5 border-b border-brand-border/60 pb-4">
      <div class="text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-blue-neon">
        Legal Agreements
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-brand-text">
        Terms & Conditions<span class="text-brand-blue">.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xs text-brand-text-muted">
        Last Updated: June 11, 2026. Review rules for using SciCalcX online services.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Terms details -->
    <div class="border border-brand-border bg-brand-gray-dark/40 rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-8 space-y-6 shadow-xl backdrop-blur-sm leading-relaxed text-sm text-brand-text-muted">
      
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
          1. Acceptance of Terms
        </h2>
        <p>
          By accessing or using SciCalcX (the "Service"), you agree to be bound by these Terms & Conditions. If you do not agree to all terms, you must cease using the Service immediately.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
          2. Permitted Usage
        </h2>
        <p>
          SciCalcX is provided for educational, professional, and personal computation use. You agree not to misuse the site by uploading malicious scripts, attempting to inject code into layout engines, or scripting automated traffic flows that could degrade service reliability.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
          3. Intellectual Property
        </h2>
        <p>
          All codebase structures, UI styles, parsing logic algorithms, and brand images are the intellectual property of SciCalcX. Certain parsing algorithms and functions are distributed under open-source software licenses; consult our repository for detailed dependency licenses.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
          4. Accuracy Disclaimer
        </h2>
        <p>
          While we implement precision rounding methods to ensure calculations are as accurate as possible under standard binary float representations, SciCalcX makes no warranties regarding the accuracy of calculated output values. Calculations are provided "as-is", and we accept no liability for any engineering errors, computational losses, or academic issues arising from calculated results.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
          5. Modifications
        </h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to modify or discontinue features, sheets, or terms at any time. Your continued use of the service following such changes constitutes your acceptance of the revised terms.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
